The paper deals with the development of a novel online universal classifier capable of performing binary, multi-class, and multi-label classification. The paper involves the use of machine learning techniques and algorithms to develop the proposed classifier. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves the use of datasets, which indicates that it may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of high-speed online classifiers, which indicates that it may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
